org.jgrapes.core

Class Component

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jgrapes.core.internal.ComponentVertex
      • org.jgrapes.core.Component
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<ComponentType>, Channel, ComponentType, Eligible, Manager
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FileStorage, HandlingErrorPrinter, HttpServer, HttpServerDemo, LanguageSelector, NioDispatcher, PostProcessor, PreferencesStore, SessionManager, SslServer, StaticContentDispatcher, TcpServer, WsEchoServer

    public abstract class Component
extends ComponentVertex
implements ComponentType, Channel

    This class can be used as base class for implementing a component.

    This class implements the Manager interface. Contrary to classes that only implement ComponentType, derived classes therefore don't need a manager attribute to get access to the component management methods provided by this interface.

    This class also implements the Channel interface in such a way that each instance of this class can be used as an independent channel.

    See Also:
    ComponentType

      • Component

        public Component()

      • Component

        public Component(Channel componentChannel)

        Creates a new component base with its channel set to the given channel. As a special case Channel.SELF can be passed to the constructor to make the component use itself as channel. The special value is necessary as you obviously cannot pass an object to be constructed to its constructor.

        Parameters:
        componentChannel - the channel that the component’s handlers listen on by default and that Manager.fire(Event, Channel...) sends the event to
